         <abstract>
            <p>This paper describes the undesirable chatter which can occur in passenger car limited slip axles and compares the performance of different lubricants in these units. A bench test for evaluating limited slip gear oils is described together with a practical method for preventing chatter through the use of lubricant additives.</p>
         </abstract>
